Building the same tool on two different ecosystems taught me a lot:
The JetBrains SDK is powerful but has a steeper learning curve — 
you need to understand plugin.xml, extension points, and service 
registration
The VS Code API is simpler — package.json handles most of the 
configuration and the API surface is smaller
Publishing on JetBrains Marketplace requires a review (1-2 business days)
Publishing on VS Code Marketplace is nearly instant via .vsix upload
